        "content": "<p>One of the fields on the organization creation page is the URL to use for the org, which has a hint below the field.</p>\n<p>On Zulip Cloud:</p>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/70/YYzPQoWyQlv2075NAsdZdnWq/Screen-Shot-2022-08-23-at-8.39.52-AM.png\">Screen-Shot-2022-08-23-at-8.39.52-AM.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/70/YYzPQoWyQlv2075NAsdZdnWq/Screen-Shot-2022-08-23-at-8.39.52-AM.png\" title=\"Screen-Shot-2022-08-23-at-8.39.52-AM.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/70/YYzPQoWyQlv2075NAsdZdnWq/Screen-Shot-2022-08-23-at-8.39.52-AM.png\"></a></div><p>On a self-hosted server:<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/2/d6/ypye7ZfuDjpEpEten5zA2VbM/Screen-Shot-2022-08-23-at-8.16.49-AM.png\">Screen-Shot-2022-08-23-at-8.16.49-AM.png</a> <br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/2/45/4ZSbdUKanrUGmiXvhZcFFRA0/Screen-Shot-2022-08-23-at-8.18.29-AM.png\">Screen-Shot-2022-08-23-at-8.18.29-AM.png</a> </p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/d6/ypye7ZfuDjpEpEten5zA2VbM/Screen-Shot-2022-08-23-at-8.16.49-AM.png\" title=\"Screen-Shot-2022-08-23-at-8.16.49-AM.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/d6/ypye7ZfuDjpEpEten5zA2VbM/Screen-Shot-2022-08-23-at-8.16.49-AM.png\"></a></div><div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/45/4ZSbdUKanrUGmiXvhZcFFRA0/Screen-Shot-2022-08-23-at-8.18.29-AM.png\" title=\"Screen-Shot-2022-08-23-at-8.18.29-AM.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/45/4ZSbdUKanrUGmiXvhZcFFRA0/Screen-Shot-2022-08-23-at-8.18.29-AM.png\"></a></div><p>Do folks find that hint helpful? The wording feels a bit awkward to me, and I'm not sure how much additional value it provides over the \"Organization URL\" title for the field. Is there a history to why it was added?</p>\n<p>CC <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"21836\">@Lauryn Menard</span></p>",
        "id": 1423597,
        "sender_full_name": "Alya Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1661269371
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah I'm not sure the hint adds anything over the \"Organization URL\" title. It seems possible it was added as part of a visual design that was going for each field having a hint as a design pattern, or something like that; I don't see that as a strong reason to keep it.</p>",
        "id": 1423845,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1661294746
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's been there since <a href=\"https://github.com/zulip/zulip/commit/ea39fb25565ffdadb9060406dba60b40b2b89eac\">ea39fb25565ffdadb9060406dba60b40b2b89eac</a> (2016) when we first added support for subdomains at all, though the string got tweaked from \"the address ...\" to \"the URL\" in 2020.</p>",
        "id": 1423846,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1661294858
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Checking back in about whether people have thoughts about this hint text being helpful on the organization creation form.</p>",
